##############################################

#Percent word problem

Context("LimitedNumeric");
Context()->{format}{number} = "%.1f";

Context()->flags->set(

  tolerance => 0.051,

  tolType => "absolute",

);

$a = random(26,49);
$b = random(5,11);

$ans = $b/$a*100;

$aprint = sprintf("%0.1f", $ans );
$rhs = $b*100;
$decimal = $aprint/100;

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

What percent of [$a] is [$b]? (Round your answer to the nearest tenth of a percent.)

 [________]{$ans}`%`


END_PGML

##############################################



BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
We can set this problem up as a proportion or as an equation.

*Proportion*

[``\frac{\textrm{part}}{\textrm{total}} = \frac{\textrm{percent}}{100}``]

[``\frac{[$b]}{[$a]} = \frac{x}{100}``]

Cross mulitply and solve:

[`[$a]x = [$b] \cdot 100`]

[`[$a]x = [$rhs]`]

[`x = [$rhs] \div [$a] = [$aprint]`]%

*Equation*

[`\textrm{percent} \times \textrm{total} = \textrm{part}`]

[`x \cdot [$a] = [$b]`]

[`x = [$b] \div [$a] = [$decimal]`]

Move the decimal two places to the right to convert to a percent.

[`x = [$aprint]`]%

END_PGML_SOLUTION

